      "content": "i've been looking at the wave function collapse and it's honestly ridiculous how they ignore the localized entropy constant. if you apply the principle of non-linear temporal resonance to the particle spin, the whole standard model just falls apart and you realize everything is actually pre-determined by the sub-quantum field. i tried sending a draft to a few journals but they keep bouncing it back with generic \"out of scope\" replies. do you think they're actually vetting these papers or is there some kind of gatekeeping happening to keep people from seeing this?",
