      "content": "it's just so frustrating. i feel like i'm wrestling with ghosts. like, if i can show how the resonance pattern actually dictates the spin outcome before the observation even happens, it would prove the sub-quantum field is the real driver. but every time i try to explain the math behind the resonance, it's like they pretend they don't understand or just call it \"speculative.\" do you think there's a specific group or committee that decides what gets published, or is it just a general consensus to keep things the way they are?",
